From cou.: 52 The concentration profiles are most easily studied in conformal space. This is because the greatest changes in concentration and in potential occur close to the electrode surface. The x axis is completely occupied by the electrode in the conformal space but is only partially occupied in real space. However, Fig. 6–9 are included in real space to enable comparisons to be made with the following discussions in conformal space.
From Soup: 52 For the cyclic voltammetry and chronoamperometry experiments, 2.0 mM [Ru(NH 3 ) 6 ]Cl 3 or K 2 IrCl 6 solutions in ultrapure water with a resistivity of >18.2 MΩ cm −1 (20 °C) were prepared, at different concentrations of the supporting electrolyte, KCl. Solutions were outgassed with N 2 before experiments and a positive pressure of N 2 was maintained throughout.
