From cou.: 60 As explained in the Theory section, this relation becomes increasingly unreliable as the electrochemical rate constant, K0, decreases.25,27Fig. 10(b) shows the percentage error between the simulation for a microdisc and for a hemisphere using the hemispherical approximation. The maximum error is shown to be 3.81%: close to the error range of most experiments. The hemispherical approximation is therefore quantitatively useful when K0 < 10−3. Since this analysis is conducted for an extreme case, this is also valid for higher support ratios and different charges in the one electron A/B redox couple.
