From cou.: 72 The simulations and the Debye–Hückel theory are used to analyze cyclic voltammetry obtained for two aqueous redox couples: hexaammineruthenium [Ru(NH3)6]3+/[Ru(NH3)6]2+ and hexachloroiridate [IrCl6]2−/[IrCl6]3−. The data indicate the occurrence of ion pairing in the latter but not in the former.
